* The lyrics of British rock group [[Dire_Straits|Dire Straits]]' song ''Industrial Disease'' (from the [[Love_Over_Gold|Love Over Gold]] album) refer to Speakers' Corner: "And I go down to Speakers' Corner, I'm a-thunderstruck, they got free speech, tourists, police in trucks.  Two men say they're Jesus, one of them must be wrong.  There's a protester singing, and he's singing a protest song..."
